{"id":3650,"date":"2021-04-09T11:18:13","date_gmt":"2021-04-09T09:18:13","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/154.0.202.153\/?post_type=dt_team&#038;p=3650"},"modified":"2025-03-31T17:59:39","modified_gmt":"2025-03-31T15:59:39","slug":"karondo-kletus-3","status":"publish","type":"dt_team","link":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/dt_team\/karondo-kletus-3\/","title":{"rendered":"Karondo, Hamutenya, Kletus"},"content":{"rendered":"<table width=\"100%\" align=\"left\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-7327\" src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/k_karondo-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"136\" height=\"204\" \/><\/td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p class=\"contact-position\"><strong>Member of Parliament &#8211; National Assembly <\/strong><\/p>\n<p class=\"contact-street\">Address: Private Bag 13323, Windhoek<\/p>\n<p class=\"contact-country\">SWAPO Party<\/p>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"25%\"><strong>Legislative Profile<\/strong><\/td>\n<td valign=\"top\">A member of parliament since March 2020 and currently serving as a Chairperson of the standing committee on Constitutional and Legal affairs. A trained teacher and former principal of Rundu Secondary School,\u00a0 \u00a0promoted to the rank of inspector of education. A former unionist in NANTU who got elected to the NTC in 2006.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Personal<\/strong><\/td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Born on 12 September 1977, Windhoek<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Education<\/strong><\/td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Master of Public Policy &amp; Management (2018-2019) at the International University of Management. Bachelor of Education Honours (2003-2004) at Rhodes University. Higher Education Diploma (1993-1996) at the University of Namibia. Standard 10(Matric) 1989 at the Rundu Secondary School.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Career<\/strong><\/td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Inspector of Education, November 2007-2017 October 2019 Kavango West Region. Principal of Rundu Secondary School from January 2000 to 31 October 2007. Deputy Principal of Rundu Secondary School (1999). Teacher, Rundu Secondary School (1997-1998)<\/p>\n<p>Political: Joined SWAPO in 1987 and NANSO in 1988 while attending school at Rundu Secondary School. From 1999 onwards assisted national leaders and helped with translations and interpretations at major SWAPO Rallies and during important national events. September 2019, nominated by President Hage Geingob to the National Assembly as part of his ten nominees.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Interests<\/strong><\/td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Education, Public Policy matters, Natural Resources as well as Legal Affairs.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Member of Parliament &#8211; National Assembly Address: Private Bag 13323, Windhoek SWAPO Party Legislative Profile A member of parliament since March 2020 and currently serving as a Chairperson of the standing committee on Constitutional and Legal affairs. A trained teacher and former principal of Rundu Secondary School,\u00a0 \u00a0promoted to the rank of inspector of education.&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"featured_media":3651,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","dt_team_category":[92],"class_list":["post-3650","dt_team","type-dt_team","status-publish","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","dt_team_category-7th-national-assembly-2020-2025","dt_team_category-92","description-off"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/dt_team\/3650","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/dt_team"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/dt_team"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=3650"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.par